### Pages vs Static Files:

Webgoose differentiates Pages from Files using only file extensions.

The following files are picked up as pages:
- `.md`
- `.webgoose`

Anything else is considered a static file, and is simply copied to its build destination.

Some of these extensions have special meaning, please see the "File Extensions & Their Meanings" Section in the "Less Quick Start" for more info.




