### File Extensions & Their Meanings:

As covered in the Quick Start, anything that is a `.md` or `.webgoose` file is considered a page.

However, each of these has a special meaning:

- `.md` - Page will be processed normally

- `.webgoose` - The page will be evaluated as potentially multiple pages (see *"Dynamic File Creation"* section)

